package.json is configuration settings and a list of dependencies required for the project to run

The package.json file is crucial for setting up, configuring, and documenting Node.js projects.

The package-lock.json file is a file generated by npm that provides a detailed, version-locked representation of the project's dependencies.

Always put package and package.lock you can recreate your node_modules. by doing npm install

Just like we have npm, we have npx. npx means executing the package. npm is used to install a package

npm run start to start project after writing script in your package.json

